      • define

        public void define(Symbol sym)
        Description copied from interface: Scope
        Define a symbol in this scope, throw IllegalArgumentException if sym already defined in this scope. This alters sym: 1. Set insertion order number of sym 2. Set sym's scope to be the scope. The order in which symbols are defined must be preserved so that Scope.getSymbols() returns the list in definition order.
